e parameters of political correctness by engaging in a dialogue that refutes these postulations in a direct, frontal debate. In this volume, as well as in the forthcoming volume, The Possibility of Pluralism, eminent scholars from around the world explore notions of pluralism, discussing the broad spectrum of its relevance and application to modern day societies, from secularism and multiculturalism to democracy, globalisation and the pivotal role of civil society."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCultural pluralismxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aIslamic civilization. 0aMuslimsxSocial conditions. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Cultural Policy.2bisacsh1 aBilgrami, Akeel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaher, Adel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFilali-Ansary, Abdou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarmali Ahmed, Sikeena, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMohsin, Amena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYalman, Nur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZubaida, Sami, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aal-Azmeh, Aziz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aal-Sayyid, Ridwan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074863969440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074864209040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748642090423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748642090/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013